If a bank already uses a third-party platform like CUBE for regulatory intelligence, then proposing a generic regulatory automation idea in a hackathon may not stand out unless you take a fresh angle or go beyond what CUBE already offers.

Here‚Äôs how to position it smartly:

‚∏ª

When It‚Äôs NOT a Good Idea (As-Is)
	‚Ä¢	If your idea just replicates regulatory document parsing, tracking regulation changes, or basic compliance mapping ‚Äî CUBE already does this at scale.
	‚Ä¢	Judges might dismiss the idea as redundant or lacking innovation if it mirrors existing vendor features.

‚∏ª

When It‚Äôs a GOOD Hackathon Idea

If you extend or complement what CUBE or other platforms do, then yes, it‚Äôs a great opportunity. Here are angles that would make it valuable:

1. Intelligent Control Testing Layer
	‚Ä¢	Take the regulations that CUBE maps to policies and create a GenAI/NLP-based solution that automatically suggests test cases or risk controls to be validated.
	‚Ä¢	Focus: bridging regulatory obligations with practical testing logic and assurance execution.

2. Narrative-Based Non-Compliance Detection
	‚Ä¢	Analyze issue logs, emails, or narratives to detect potential breaches of mapped regulations.
	‚Ä¢	This creates a real-time surveillance layer using GenAI ‚Äî something even CUBE may not offer directly.

3. Regulatory Impact Forecaster
	‚Ä¢	Build a prototype to forecast which controls or business lines will be most impacted by upcoming regulations using historical trends + regulatory intelligence.
	‚Ä¢	Adds a predictive lens to the existing static mapping.

4. Internal Use Case Discovery Bot
	‚Ä¢	Use GenAI to read through past audit reports, issue logs, and findings to surface recurring themes and suggest enhancements to existing regulatory mappings.

5. Visualization + Prioritization Engine
	‚Ä¢	A real-time dashboard that integrates control effectiveness, regulation severity, and recent breaches ‚Äî for risk-weighted prioritization of compliance efforts.

‚∏ª

How to Pitch It in the Hackathon

‚ÄúWhile we already use advanced regulatory tech, our idea is to build an intelligent layer that enhances the value of existing platforms by transforming static regulatory mapping into dynamic, actionable insights for assurance and control testing.‚Äù

